2
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:37,400
I'm Gigi Murin!

3
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:41,200
I used to be 14 years old in 8th grade, but now I'm not!

4
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,300
I'm a bit clumsy, crazy and silly, and I may not look it,

5
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,500
but actually, I'm a member of Hololive English Justice.

6
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,800
That's true.

7
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,800
I literally call myself the Fister because I fister people with my big big power glyph,

8
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:55,200
and the citizens don't really like that I call myself the Fister,

9
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,000
and I don't really know why.

10
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:05,500
TWO GREMS AND A SHOEBOX

11
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,300
Literally called the Fister because I fister people, you know?

12
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:10,500
You know what I mean?

13
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,300
Today's the day of a very important Justice meeting,

14
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,200
but I- I accidentally overslept!

15
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,200
So I have to hurry up and...

16
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:21,800
make sure to look both ways before crossing the road!

17
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,000
And go!

18
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:24,500
Ah!

19
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,500
Gigi goes bye-bye!

20
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:32,000
Ah! Ouch!

21
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:38,500
Who is that? That was so weird.

22
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,800
Wow! Where am I?

23
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,000
Beautiful 2D fantasy world!

24
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,500
I'm so efficient at doing things in my car...

25
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,300
Hit them with a car and it'd be really cool... what the...?

26
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,200
A horse? That's not a truck.

27
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,000
That's dangerous! I could have died!

28
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:10,200
But phew! That Grem sure knows how to drive.

29
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:11,200
Gremlin Justi-

30
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,500
Ah!

31
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:26,500
Ugh... my body hurts.

32
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:33,500
I feel like I got run over by something, but I don't know what.

33
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:38,500
Oh! Is that a statue of a Grem? Looks cool.

34
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Wait a second... I know this!

35
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,000
I've been Isekai'd!

36
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:48,000
What the freak! Gigi, you're here too?

37
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,500
This Justice cardboard...

38
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Gigi, what's going on? Where are we?

39
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,000
What are you guys doing? Why are you cardboard?

40
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,500
Why does Cece look so sad?

41
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,500
You f***ing h**! How dare you do this to me!

42
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:08,500
You b***h! This is your fault somehow!

43
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:12,500
I don't know how you did this, you absolute little d***head! Oh, you look terrible!

44
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Well, let's go investigate around here!

45
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,200
Let's go! Okay! I'm on my way!

46
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,500
Wait, guys! Wait for me!

47
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:24,500
We can have an adventure together! It'll be so fun and...

48
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:30,500
Wait, wait! What's going on?

49
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Ahhhhh!

50
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:37,500
Horses!

51
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:41,500
Two of them!

52
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:52,000
Ahhhhh!

53
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,800
Goodbye,

54
00:04:55,800 --> 00:05:01,000
leaving heartbreak of the past behind

55
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,008
Looking back

56
00:05:01,008 --> 00:05:02,008
it's time

57
00:05:02,008 --> 00:05:03,908
Moving down our own path

58
00:05:03,908 --> 00:05:07,008
Evermore voyaging forward

59
00:05:07,008 --> 00:05:10,508
To make this journey last

60
00:05:23,008 --> 00:05:29,008
GIGI MURIN

61
00:05:29,808 --> 00:05:33,108
In a sparkle within the light

62
00:05:33,508 --> 00:05:36,708
Like a promise found riding the wind

63
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:41,008
Where a myth begins spiraling outward and up

64
00:05:41,008 --> 00:05:44,208
An inspiring tale begins

65
00:05:44,508 --> 00:05:48,308
We who dared defy changing of times

66
00:05:48,508 --> 00:05:52,008
As we follow unreachable dreams

67
00:05:52,008 --> 00:05:55,208
Know it's here and right now

68
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:56,508
That we're drawn to somehow

69
00:05:56,508 --> 00:06:00,008
Deep inside a will to live believe

70
00:06:02,808 --> 00:06:06,008
Wandering near and far

71
00:06:06,508 --> 00:06:10,008
Touching lives just like ours

72
00:06:10,008 --> 00:06:13,508
Finding fires

73
00:06:13,508 --> 00:06:15,508
Till they've wasted away

74
00:06:15,508 --> 00:06:17,008
One day

75
00:06:17,508 --> 00:06:21,008
I'll recall this night

76
00:06:21,008 --> 00:06:24,508
Our relentless odyssey

77
00:06:24,508 --> 00:06:27,508
Pressing onward

78
00:06:27,508 --> 00:06:31,508
We never surrender

79
00:06:31,508 --> 00:06:35,508
Toward the skies we can rise

80
00:06:35,508 --> 00:06:39,008
Again

81
00:06:43,008 --> 00:06:47,008
Again

82
00:07:03,008 --> 00:07:08,508
ううう... ああ...
Uuuh... Aah...

83
00:07:08,508 --> 00:07:11,808
これ以上何かにぶつかったら
If anything else hits me,

84
00:07:11,808 --> 00:07:14,308
もう長くは持たないと思う...
I don't think I'll survive much longer...

85
00:07:14,308 --> 00:07:17,008
本当にもっと気をつけないと
I really need to be more careful.

86
00:07:17,008 --> 00:07:19,508
生きててよかった
Thank goodness I'm still alive.

87
00:07:19,508 --> 00:07:24,008
風がお前の訪れを囁いていた...
The winds whispered of your coming...

88
00:07:24,008 --> 00:07:28,008
そして今、お前はここにいる
And now, here you are.

89
00:07:28,508 --> 00:07:30,508
あんた誰！？
Who are you!?

90
00:07:30,508 --> 00:07:36,008
ワシはグレム王国で最も偉大な魔法使い
I am the greatest wizard in all of Grem Kingdom.

91
00:07:36,508 --> 00:07:39,008
魔法使いおじいちゃんだ
Wizard Oji-chan.

92
00:07:39,008 --> 00:07:41,508
魔法使いおじいちゃん？
Wizard Oji-chan?

93
00:07:41,508 --> 00:07:43,508
魔法使いなの、おじいちゃんなの？
Are you a wizard or Oji-chan?

94
00:07:43,508 --> 00:07:46,008
名前はあるの？何て呼べばいい？
Do you have a name? What should I call you?

95
00:07:46,008 --> 00:07:50,508
多くのグレムの戦士たちが一人、また一人と倒れていった
So many of Grem's warriors have fallen, one by one,

96
00:07:50,508 --> 00:07:54,008
お前の到着を待つ間に...
while we waited for your arrival...

97
00:07:54,008 --> 00:07:55,508
オッケー
Okay.

98
00:07:55,508 --> 00:07:57,008
待った甲斐があった！
The wait was worth it!!!

99
00:07:57,008 --> 00:07:58,508
ジジ！
Gigi!

100
00:07:58,508 --> 00:08:03,508
お前はワシが想像したどんな英雄よりもはるかに強力だ！
You are far more powerful than I ever imagined a hero could be!

101
00:08:04,008 --> 00:08:06,008
返事してくれないな。たぶんNPCだ
He's not responding to me. He's probably an NPC.

102
00:08:06,008 --> 00:08:08,508
これってゲーム？ゲームみたいな感じ？
It's like this is a game? Like a game?

103
00:08:08,508 --> 00:08:10,508
NPC！？
NPC!?

104
00:08:11,008 --> 00:08:13,508
NPCだと！？
NPC!?

105
00:08:13,508 --> 00:08:16,008
わあ、ごめんなさい！ごめんなさい！
Oh, I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

106
00:08:16,508 --> 00:08:18,508
ワシは高貴な魔法使いだぞ！
I am the noble wizard!

107
00:08:18,508 --> 00:08:20,508
おじいちゃんだぞ！
Oji-chan!

108
00:08:20,508 --> 00:08:24,008
ごめんなさい！喋れるなんて知らなかったの！
Oh, I'm sorry! I didn't know you could talk!

109
00:08:25,008 --> 00:08:27,508
お前が鍵なのだ
You're the key.

110
00:08:27,508 --> 00:08:31,008
お前がいなければ、お前の友もこの世界も
Without you, your friend and this world

111
00:08:31,008 --> 00:08:34,508
失われてしまう...
are lost...

112
00:08:34,508 --> 00:08:38,008
えっ？失われる？何の話？
What? Lost? What are you talking about?

113
00:08:38,008 --> 00:08:39,508
ジジよ
Gigi,

114
00:08:39,508 --> 00:08:42,508
世界が待っている...
the world is waiting...

115
00:08:42,508 --> 00:08:44,508
私の名前を知ってるの？
He knows my name.

116
00:08:44,508 --> 00:08:46,508
それ、私。私がヒーローなんだ
That's me. I'm the hero.

117
00:08:46,508 --> 00:08:51,508
世界を... 段ボールになることから救うんだ！
I'm going to save the world from... from being cardboard!

118
00:08:52,508 --> 00:08:56,508
ハズァーーーーッ！！
HAZZAAHH!!

119
00:08:56,508 --> 00:08:59,008
うわああ、私に何をしたの！？
Aaah, what did you do to me!?

120
00:08:59,008 --> 00:09:01,008
痛い！痛いよ！
It hurts! It hurts!

121
00:09:01,008 --> 00:09:03,008
おかしいな...
That's strange...

122
00:09:03,008 --> 00:09:05,508
何て言ってるの？何で痛いの？
What are you saying? Why does it hurt?

123
00:09:05,508 --> 00:09:09,008
ハズァッ！！
HAZZAA!!

124
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:14,008
わあ！私、すごく可愛くて柔らかくてふわふわになった！
Wow! I'm so cute and soft and fluffy now!

125
00:09:14,008 --> 00:09:16,508
お友達になりましょう！在庫がある時に買ってね！
Friends with you! Purchase next time they're in stock!

126
00:09:16,508 --> 00:09:18,508
ごめん、もう一回やらせて！
Sorry, let me try again!

127
00:09:18,508 --> 00:09:20,508
今度はちゃんとやるから！
I'll do it right this time!

128
00:09:20,508 --> 00:09:21,808
よくわからないけど...
I don't understand...

129
00:09:21,808 --> 00:09:24,008
オッケー、オッケー！
Okay, okay!

130
00:09:24,008 --> 00:09:29,508
ハズァーーーーッ！！
HAZZAAHH!!

131
00:09:32,008 --> 00:09:34,008
スクイーク！スクイークスクイーク！
Squeak! Squeak squeak!

132
00:09:34,008 --> 00:09:37,508
どうした、もっと強くなりたいか！？
What's wrong, you want to be more powerful!?

133
00:09:38,008 --> 00:09:40,508
よーし、いいぞ！準備はいいか！？
Okay, okay! I'm ready!

134
00:09:41,008 --> 00:09:44,508
ジジ！行くぞ、ボディー！
Gigi! Here we go, body!

135
00:09:44,508 --> 00:09:48,508
パアアアア！！
PAAAAHH!!

136
00:09:51,008 --> 00:09:55,008
ううう... ああ...
Uuuh... Aah...

137
00:09:55,008 --> 00:09:59,008
あ、待って！動けるようになった！
Oh wait! I can move now!

138
00:10:01,516 --> 00:10:02,516
What's this?

139
00:10:03,016 --> 00:10:04,016
Hands!

140
00:10:04,016 --> 00:10:05,516
You did it! You've done it!

141
00:10:06,516 --> 00:10:09,516
Oh my god, look how... how cute I am.

142
00:10:10,516 --> 00:10:13,016
Aww, I've always been cute, but now...

143
00:10:13,016 --> 00:10:15,516
now it's even cute... now everyone can see how cute I am.

144
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:18,516
Look at that fat tail. Look at that fat tail.

145
00:10:19,016 --> 00:10:20,516
I can do everything!

146
00:10:20,516 --> 00:10:21,516
I can't do that.

147
00:10:22,016 --> 00:10:24,016
Watch this, guys. You've never seen this before.

148
00:10:24,016 --> 00:10:27,516
Okay, okay. Whee! Whee! I can do everything.

149
00:10:28,016 --> 00:10:30,016
Two in a row? Just kidding.

150
00:10:30,016 --> 00:10:32,016
I have a world to save.

151
00:10:32,016 --> 00:10:34,016
Look at that! Everyone loves me!

152
00:10:35,016 --> 00:10:36,516
Gigi Murin! Hahaha!

153
00:10:48,016 --> 00:10:49,016
Oh, dizzy.

154
00:10:49,016 --> 00:10:51,016
Wizard: Oh, I'm so dizzy.

155
00:10:52,016 --> 00:10:54,016
Wizard: Oh, oh, I'm sorry.

156
00:10:55,016 --> 00:10:57,516
What... what should I do to save everyone?

157
00:11:02,016 --> 00:11:04,016
Oh, the world is spinning. Owie.

158
00:11:06,016 --> 00:11:08,516
Wizard: Before saving everyone...

159
00:11:08,516 --> 00:11:11,516
let's see if you can survive basic chores.

160
00:11:12,016 --> 00:11:13,516
Basic? I can do basic chores.

161
00:11:15,516 --> 00:11:17,516
Wizard: Let's start with...

162
00:11:21,016 --> 00:11:23,016
Start with what? Start with what?

163
00:11:23,016 --> 00:11:24,516
What? What are we starting with?

164
00:11:25,016 --> 00:11:27,016
What? What? A wing?

165
00:11:30,016 --> 00:11:32,516
Wait! Wait! What did you do? What did you do?

166
00:11:33,016 --> 00:11:35,516
Oh, did you do something? Wait! Ah!

167
00:11:40,016 --> 00:11:42,016
Wait! Wait! Wait!

168
00:11:42,516 --> 00:11:44,516
No! No!

169
00:11:49,516 --> 00:11:51,516
The birds took him.

170
00:11:51,516 --> 00:11:54,016
I knew I could never trust a bird.

171
00:11:55,016 --> 00:11:57,516
Sewer Grem: Hey you. Come here! Follow me!

172
00:11:58,016 --> 00:11:58,516
A Grem?

173
00:11:59,516 --> 00:12:02,016
Um... but I have to help my... friend.

174
00:12:03,016 --> 00:12:06,016
Sewer Grem: You're scared and lost... Not knowing what to do, right?

175
00:12:07,016 --> 00:12:09,516
Sewer Grem: I'll show you how to save your friends. Follow me!

176
00:12:10,016 --> 00:12:11,016
Oh, okay.

177
00:12:13,016 --> 00:12:14,516
So small.

178
00:12:24,516 --> 00:12:26,016
This is weird.

179
00:12:28,016 --> 00:12:30,516
This place is dark and it smells bad.

180
00:12:31,516 --> 00:12:33,516
Sewer Grem: Hey it smells good!!!!

181
00:12:33,516 --> 00:12:35,516
Do exactly as I say if you want to save your friends!

182
00:12:36,016 --> 00:12:39,516
Sewer Grem: Go to the Grem Kingdom and return with the One Ping, a Honkshoe, and a Straw Hat.

183
00:12:40,016 --> 00:12:41,516
Why do you need them?

184
00:12:42,016 --> 00:12:45,016
Sewer Grem: YOU DON'T GET TO ASK ME ANY QUESTIONS!!! NOW GO GIGI, GOOOOOOO!!

185
00:12:47,516 --> 00:12:48,516
Okay.

186
00:13:01,516 --> 00:13:03,016
Whoa!

187
00:13:03,016 --> 00:13:05,516
So this is the Grem Kingdom?

188
00:13:06,016 --> 00:13:09,016
It's so cool. There's so many Grems!

189
00:13:09,516 --> 00:13:13,016
Does this mean this entire kingdom is mine if I save it?

190
00:13:15,016 --> 00:13:17,016
Whoa, there's so many of you.

191
00:13:20,516 --> 00:13:22,016
What? No, not all at once. No, no, no.

192
00:13:22,016 --> 00:13:24,016
What? Oh, I can't hear you.

193
00:13:24,516 --> 00:13:27,516
Let's... let's try this Grem. Lucky little Grem, what's on your mind?

194
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:32,516
Grem NPC: Things aren't going well with my partner... I need your help to fix our relationship.

195
00:13:33,516 --> 00:13:36,016
Aww... that is not my problem.

196
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:41,016
Ah, okay. How about this Grem? Do you have anything interesting to say to me?

197
00:13:42,016 --> 00:13:44,516
Grem NPC: My tummy is getting very large and I don't know why.

198
00:13:44,516 --> 00:13:47,016
Please come with me to the doctor.

199
00:13:49,016 --> 00:13:52,516
(Whispering) Okay, a little secret... pregnant.

200
00:13:53,016 --> 00:13:55,016
Okay, how about this one?

201
00:13:56,016 --> 00:13:59,016
Grem NPC: Make a contract with me, and become a magical girl!

202
00:14:00,016 --> 00:14:04,016
Oh, that is not my problem either. Oh no, no, no, no.

203
00:14:04,016 --> 00:14:07,016
I will not be doing that. I know what happens when you sign a contract.

204
00:14:07,516 --> 00:14:10,016
You should never put your name down on things.

205
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:13,016
Well, these Grems were useless.

206
00:14:13,016 --> 00:14:15,516
I think if I use my RPG knowledge, you're supposed to get information from NPCs...

207
00:14:15,516 --> 00:14:18,016
at a store!

208
00:14:19,016 --> 00:14:20,516
at a store!

209
00:14:20,516 --> 00:14:22,516
And there's so many stalls near me. Ah, I'll go to this one.

210
00:14:29,516 --> 00:14:31,016
Aww, so cute.

211
00:14:31,516 --> 00:14:35,016
Aww, are you a little worker Grem? Aww.

212
00:14:35,516 --> 00:14:37,516
How much do you make an hour? Do you even make enough to survive?

213
00:14:40,016 --> 00:14:42,016
Aww. Oh, what is this?

214
00:14:43,016 --> 00:14:45,016
Ooh, for me?

215
00:14:47,016 --> 00:14:49,016
General Store Grem: Uh, that's decorative hay, not edible...

216
00:14:54,516 --> 00:14:56,016
Could I ask you something?

217
00:14:57,016 --> 00:14:59,016
Oh, what is this? Dialogue!

218
00:15:02,124 --> 00:15:03,224
Um...

219
00:15:03,224 --> 00:15:05,824
Where can I get The One Ping?

220
00:15:07,024 --> 00:15:08,524
Oh you are looking for the One Ping?

221
00:15:08,824 --> 00:15:10,524
Then, here is the Quest for you!

222
00:15:10,524 --> 00:15:12,024
